HEADWORD: Controversialist
<hw>Con`tro*ver"sial*ist</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One who carries on a
controversy; a disputant.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He [Johnson] was both intellectually and morally of the stuff of
which <qex>controversialists</qex> are made.</q>
<rj><qau>Macaulay.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Controversially</ent>⟦br⟧
